The+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2811%2F21%2F24%29&utm_content=3DT=
he+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2811%2F18%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Dema=
il_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) weeks ag=
o on CNN that Trump, after choosing loyalist disruptors like Gaetz and Hegs=
eth, and unsurprising fringe surrogates like Gabbard and Kennedy Jr., would=
 select a name brand for Treasury. And with Steve Schwarzman and Jamie Dimo=
n taking themselves out of the running, it made sense that someone like Row=
an has emerged as a dark horse. Last night, my partner Bill Cohan reported =
( https://puck.news/apollos-marc-rowan-goes-to-washington/?utm_campaign=3DT=
he+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2811%2F21%2F24%29&utm_content=3DTh=
e+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2811%2F18%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demai=
l_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) that Rowa=
n is very much in the lead. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s
his job to lose,=E2=80=9D Bill wrote. We may know as soon as the end of thi=
s week.

