The D.N.C. Slugfest

The war between the Democrats=E2=80=99 pragmatists and its big thinkers is =
playing out in the race for D.N.C. chair=E2=80=94even though that contest d=
oesn=E2=80=99t formally kick off until later next year. As I wrote last wee=
k, Democrats seeking a =E2=80=9Cfighter=E2=80=9D are pushing for Rahm Emanu=
el, the pugnacious former Chicago mayor and current ambassador to Japan. Pr=
o-Rahm chatter has emerged from disparate corners of the party=E2=80=94incl=
uding his frenemy David Axelrod on X ( https://x.com/davidaxelrod/status/18=
56746441286332513?utm_campaign=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%=
2811%2F21%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2=
811%2F18%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_ter=
m=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) and former D.C.C.C. chair Steve Israel in The Hill=
=20
( https://thehill.com/opinion/campaign/4997915-run-rahm-run-why-emanuel-sho=
uld-lead-the-dnc/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%=
2811%2F21%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2=
811%2F18%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_ter=
m=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ). =E2=80=9CNo more losers,=E2=80=9D said one former=
 D.N.C. official involved in the recruitment process. =E2=80=9CIf you lost =
[an election], you have no business telling the party how to win.=E2=80=9D

Naturally, there=E2=80=99s a burgeoning anti-Rahm contingent as well. Ken M=
artin, the head of Minnesota=E2=80=99s Democratic-Farmer-Labor Party=E2=80=
=94who most people outside of D.C. couldn=E2=80=99t pick out of lineup=E2=
=80=94launched his campaign with 83 endorsements from D.N.C. members, leadi=
ng some insiders to compare him to Keith Ellison, who consolidated early su=
pport in 2017 before eventually flaming out. Martin O=E2=80=99Malley, the f=
ormer Maryland governor, 2016 presidential candidate, and current head of t=
he Social Security Administration, also pitched himself for the
job=E2=80=94but came out of the gate with endorsements from just three comm=
ittee members from Maryland, although he only announced his bid four days a=
go. State Senator Mallory McMorrow of Michigan (and viral speech ( https://=
youtu.be/4mxWLUJeifE?feature=3Dshared&utm_campaign=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brigh=
test+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2811%2F21%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Bright=
est+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2811%2F18%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=
=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) fame) has yet to announce bu=
t is seriously considering the job, and is someone seen as a generational c=
hange agent and disruptor=E2=80=94qualities, obviously, that the D.N.C. cou=
ld benefit from.

One lingering question is whether any former presidents=E2=80=94ahem, Barac=
k Obama=E2=80=94will put their thumb on the scale. Of course, given the 202=
4 outcome, it=E2=80=99s unclear whether a Joe Biden endorsement would help =
or hurt. But Obama=E2=80=99s imprimatur would make it nearly impossible for=
 Rahm to lose. =E2=80=9CObama=E2=80=99s the X-factor. It=E2=80=99s also
where folks like Steve Israel and David Axelrod come out if they think that=
 Obama will endorse,=E2=80=9D the former official said.

